cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.PL 

The paper focuses on developing an automated approach to identify security patches in code repositories. This involves leveraging different classes of features and using Co-Training-based approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with security-relevant changes and vulnerabilities, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques such as Co-Training suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also involves monitoring code repositories, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with code changes and commits, which could be relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
